{"key":"processedPost-11834337","value":{"id":11834337,"first":11833491,"last":11856251,"when":1263577925,"utime":"01/15/10 07:52 PM","cleanedPost":"You don't seal before you sterilize.&nbsp; I insert a tyvek sleeve into the top part of the bag and then fold it accordion style so as steam wants to escape, it can, but once pressure starts to drop, the bag seals against the tyvek sleeve until you open it up to inoculate.&nbsp; It's hard to describe in words better than that, but you can see a video of it being done in my sawdust/woodchips chapter on the DVD.&nbsp; A sample clip is on my <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Sawdust-Woodchips\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">website</a>. <br />I don't use an impulse sealer.&nbsp; I make up hundreds of spawn bags per month using steel tie wire from the hardware store to seal the bags.&nbsp; I feel it's a safer seal.<br />RR"}}